10/11/2002
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- On Friday (8 November), the European Commissioner for Enlargement, Guenter Verheugen, reaffirmed EC support for the Romanian and Bulgarian bids for EU membership. 
He met separately with representatives of each country in Brussels. 
Verheugen said that EU road maps for the two countries would be presented for adoption during next month's EU summit in Copenhagen. 
Both countries seek a target date for accession of no later than 1 January 2007. 
(BTA, Rompres - 09/11/02)
